<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910319-0035</DOCNO><DOCID>910319-0035.</DOCID><HL>   Royal Trustco to Raise   Up to $173.3 Million   From a Rights Offering</HL><DATE>03/19/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   T.RYL TFC.A</CO><IN>DIVERSIFIED FINANCIAL SERVICES, FANNIE MAE, FREDDIE MAC (FIS)</IN><LP>   TORONTO -- Royal Trustco Ltd. said it plans to raise asmuch as 200 million Canadian dollars (US$173.3 million)through a rights offering.   Under the terms of the offering, the financial servicesconcern, controlled by Toronto's Bronfman family, will issueshareholders with one right for each share held. Five rightswill allow the shareholder to buy one common share of RoyalTrustco for C$7.75 before April 17.</LP><TEXT>   Royal Trustco has said previously that the proceeds of theissue will be used to strengthen the company's capital base.Following the offering, the company's risk-based capitalratio will be about 9.5%, up from about 8% previously. Theminimum ratio required is 7.25%.   The financial services company announced its intention toissue rights in February, after reporting a substantialfourth-quarter loss of C$251 million, or C$2.17 a share.Trilon Financial Corp., which holds a 49% stake in RoyalTrustco, will exercise its rights, the company saidpreviously.   In trading on the Toronto Stock Exchange yesterday, RoyalTrustco shares closed at C$9, off 12.5 Canadian cents.</TEXT></DOC>